helper-scripts:

These scripts don't implement the benchmarks or tools, but support the setup &
execution of them.

pbench-register-tool: tell pbench you want to use this tool
pbench-register-tool-set: tell pbench you want to use this set of tools
pbench-list-tools: tell me what tools I have registered
pbench-clear-tools: clear all tools or filter by name or group
pbench-kill-tools: kill any running tools, should you abort a benchmark before it
                   calls stop-tools
pbench-start-tools: tell pbench to start your registered tools (can be from
                    cmdline or can be called from a benchmark script)
pbench-stop-tools: same as above, but stop
pbench-postprocess-tools: format the data collected from running the tools,
                   including d3.js graphs
pbench-avg-stddev: calculate average and standard deviation gievn a sample of inputs
                   (used by benchmark scripts)
pbench-clear-results: delete all benchmark results that are in /var/lib/pbench
pbench-cleanup: clean up everything, including results and what tools have been
                registered
pbench-move-results: move result tar ball to archive results host
pbench-copy-results: same as above, but don't remove the local data
